  "prompt": "How can I watch the Shorty Awards on TV in the US?",
  "response": "The Shorty Awards, which celebrate the best in social media, digital, and influencers, typically do not have a dedicated television broadcast. Instead, the event is often live-streamed online, allowing viewers to watch from their computers, tablets, or smartphones. To watch the Shorty Awards, you can:\n\n1. **Visit the Official Website:** Go to the Shorty Awards official website for information on the live stream. They usually provide details on how to watch the event online.\n   \n2. **Check Social Media:** Follow the Shorty Awards on social media platforms like Twitter, Facebook, and Instagram. They often share updates and links to the live stream on these platforms.\n\n3. **YouTube Live:** The Shorty Awards may also stream the event live on their official YouTube channel. You can subscribe to the channel and set notifications to be alerted when the live stream starts.\n\n4. **Event Platforms:** Sometimes, the awards may be streamed on specific event-hosting platforms such as Vimeo, Twitch, or other streaming services. Check their website for the latest details.\n\nEnsure you have a stable internet connection for the best viewing experience. If the event becomes available on a television network or through a streaming service that can be accessed via smart TVs, the Shorty Awards would likely announce these details in advance.",
